The 69th question:
Prove that according to Hölder's inequality:
$$
\left(\sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{n}} \frac{1}{|\mathrm{z}-\mathrm{k}|}\right)^{2} \cdot\left(\sum_{\mathrm{k}=1}^{\mathrm{n}}|\mathrm{z}-\mathrm{k}|^{2}\right) \geq \mathrm{n}^{3} \Rightarrow \sum_{\mathrm{k}=1}^{\mathrm{n}} \frac{1}{|\mathrm{z}-\mathrm{k}|} \geq \sqrt{\frac{\mathrm{n}^{3}}{\sum_{k=1}^{\mathrm{n}}|\mathrm{z}-\mathrm{k}|^{2}}}
$$

Let \( N=\left\{z \in C\left|\sum_{k=1}^{n}\right| z-\left.k\right|^{2} \leq n^{3}\right\} \), then \( N \subseteq M \).
Also, because
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\sum_{\mathrm{k}=1}^{\mathrm{n}}|\mathrm{z}-\mathrm{k}|^{2}=\sum_{\mathrm{k}=1}^{\mathrm{n}}(\mathrm{z}-\mathrm{k})(\overline{\mathrm{z}}-\mathrm{k})=\sum_{\mathrm{k}=1}^{\mathrm{n}}\left[\mathrm{z}^{2}-(\mathrm{z}+\overline{\mathrm{z}}) \mathrm{k}+\mathrm{k}^{2}\right] \\
=\mathrm{nz}^{2}-\frac{\mathrm{n}(\mathrm{n}+1)(\mathrm{z}+\mathrm{z})}{2}+\frac{\mathrm{n}(\mathrm{n}+1)(2 \mathrm{n}+1)}{6}
\end{array}
$$

Therefore,
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\sum_{k=1}^{n}|z-k|^{2} \leq n^{3} \\
\Leftrightarrow n z^{2}-\frac{n(n+1)(z+\bar{z})}{2}+\frac{n(n+1)(2 n+1)}{6} \leq n^{3} \\
\Leftrightarrow z^{2}-\frac{(n+1)(z+\bar{z})}{2}+\frac{(n+1)(2 n+1)}{6} \leq n^{2} \\
\Leftrightarrow\left(z-\frac{n+1}{2}\right)^{(}\left(\bar{z}-\frac{n+1}{2}\right)-\frac{(n+1)^{2}}{4}+\frac{(n+1)(2 n+1)}{6} \leq n^{2}
\end{array}
$$
$$
\Leftrightarrow\left|z-\frac{\mathrm{n}+1}{2}\right| \leq \sqrt{\frac{11 \mathrm{n}^{2}+1}{12}}
$$

This shows that all points within the circle centered at \(\frac{n+1}{2}\) with radius \(\sqrt{\frac{11 n^{2}+1}{12}}\) are contained within the region \(\Omega\), thus \( S \geq \frac{\left(11 \mathrm{n}^{2}+1\right) \pi}{12} \), and the proposition is proved!

